Fellow Oldies:

My son and I (mostly him!) are finishing off my new Bergmann 1835cc long
block.  When we went to put the manifold and carb on, we found that the
progressive carb choke tends to hit the fan shroud, and that the fuel pump
is in the way.  We are using one of those Brosol fuel pumps that has the 4
screws on top and I guess can be rebuilt.

Anyone know which fuel pump will allow a progressive to sit on top with
adequate clearance?  I assume it will be one of those Brazilian/Mexican
cheapies, but which one? My local FLAPS (???, what is that)
Parts-For-Imports/Foreign Aid, has at least a couple different
models/brands.

Thanks in advance.

Curt


